item.title: 【YOUTUBE】WEB-RiP - Falling Reverse - Watch The World Burn [4K] - 5.1 DTS-HD MA
item.description:
Video 1: Youtube Untouched [4K] - Rip (by me) with AV1 Codec
Video 2: Youtube Untouched [4K] - Rip (by me) with VP9 Codec

Audio in Both Videos:
Audio Track 1: 5.1 DTS-HD MA @ 3216 kbps (Created by me from Audio Track 2*)
Audio Track 2: 2.0 LPCM @ 1536 kbps created from Original Flac (Lossless Audio)

Subtitles in Both Videos:
SRT-Subs (English), ripped as VTT-Subs from Youtube, converted to SRT-Subs

* 5.1 DTS-HD MA:
--------------------------
- Lossless Flac from Tidal => Resampled 44 Khz to 48 Khz with Adobe Audition (Highest Quality) = Audio Track 2 !!!
- Split Audio Track 2 into separate Left and Right Channel / Track with Adobe Audition (for using it as Front Channels).
- Put a little hall effect to Audio Track 2 (Stereo) and split it again for using it as Left / Right Surround Channels.
- Extracted the Center Channel, seperated it into two single Tracks, Bounced them together in one Final Center Track.
- Created a Mono Track from Audio Track 2, applied Adobe Auditions Parametric Equalizer with spezial settings = LFE Track.
- Result: 6 single Tracks used for creation of the 5.1 DTS-HD MA Audio = Audio Track 1.

Both Audio Tracks were dubbed with the correct Delay in order to Sync with the Video.
